observations.recommendation:
We recommended and the Local Chief Executive (LCE) agreed to direct the:

Municipal Accountant to prepare PPELCs and CIPLCs, and the OIC-GSO to maintain complete duly accomplished updated PCs to record all procurement and disposals of PPEs so that a reconciliation between the PCs with the physical count can be made;
Municipal Accountant and the OIC-GSO to conduct periodic reconciliation of the accounting and property records with the physical count and make the necessary adjustments on any discrepancies noted, for accurate and fair presentation of PPE account balances in the financial statement;
Concerned officials to ensure timely submission of complete RPCPPE to the Office of the Auditor; and
Municipal Accountant to exert more effort in retrieving records pertaining to various PPE accounts without depreciation and thereafter prepare the necessary journal entries to take up the depreciation for the current year, update the related Accumulated Depreciation account as well as record adjustments in the Government Equity Account for PY depreciation expenses not previously recorded.

We recommended and the Local Chief Executive (LCE) agreed to direct the Municipal Accountant to: 

Exert more efforts to secure the documents supporting the prior years’ reconciling items and cause the immediate recording of the reconciling items particularly those which persisted in the BRS for a long period;

For current year and onwards, analyze and verify discrepancies or errors and other reconciling items immediately after the preparation of the monthly BRS, and prepare JEV for corrections/adjustments in the GL to present accurate balances of the cash in bank accounts;

Provide details of the outstanding checks in the BRS for easy monitoring of its validity; 

Submit to the Auditor the monthly BRS of one account without BRS, and henceforth ensure that monthly BRS of all bank accounts are submitted to the Audit Team within the prescribed period pursuant to COA Circular No. 96-011 and Section 74 of P.D. No. 1445; 

Observe appropriate procedure set by Section 44 of Volume I of the Manual on the New Government Accounting System for LGUs to ensure proper timing of disbursements and adhere with generally accepted accounting principles and in accordance with pertinent laws and regulations in recording transactions.

Enroll the Municipality’s accounts under the LBP weAccess facility inorder to obtain copy/ies of bank statements at the earliest possible time; and

Cause the submission of BRS under General Fund with Account Number Nos. 3292-1040-30 and 48.

We recommended and the Local Chief Executive (LCE) agreed to direct the:

Municipal Accountant to ensure that perpetual inventory method is observed in the accounting for inventories;

OIC-General Services Officer to conduct complete periodic physical count of inventory on hand to pave way for any necessary adjustments in the books; 

Engineering Office to prepare the list of completed projects and submit the same to the Accounting Office for reconciliation and reclassification of Construction Materials Inventory account; and

Municipal Accountant and the OIC-General Services Officer to maintain the required forms, records and periodic reports for the recognition of expense portion of the inventories and to reconcile the same.

We recommended the Local Chief Executive (LCE) to direct the: 

Municipal Engineer to validate projects with no details/schedules and issue Certificate of Completion of the validated projects to be used as basis by the Municipal Accountant in there classification to their PPE account; 

Municipal Engineer to coordinate with the Municipal Accountant after project validation/inspection so that the proper adjustments may be made to the CIP accounts;

Municipal Accountant to maintain subsidiary ledgers for the CIP accounts, reclassify all completed projects from Construction in Progress account to appropriate asset accounts and to take up the corresponding depreciation expenses of the completed projects from the time these were completed until December 31, 2021;

The Registry of Public Infrastructure should also be maintained where the completed public infrastructures shall be transferred as provided for under Section 23 of the same manual; and

All completed assets should be closed to the appropriate asset accounts while completed public infrastructure should be transferred to the respective accounts. Likewise, at the end of the year, completed public infrastructure should be closed to Government Equity and recorded in the respective registries or RPI.

7.10   We recommended the Local Chief Executive to direct the following:
The concerned municipal officials and employees to submit the lacking supporting documents;
All other personnel concerned to refund the excess amount of travel claimed;
The Municipal Accountant to ensure the completeness and integrity of the supporting documents and the correctness of the amount claimed for diems before processing them for reimbursement; and
Municipal officials and employees to strictly adhere to the applicable rules and regulations on the allowable rates for official travel so as to avoid the incurrence of irregular expenditures.

14.9 We recommended and the Local Chief Executive (LCE) agreed to direct the Gender and Development Focal Point System (GFPS) and others concerned to:
Ensure strict adherence to the requirements outlined in JMC 2013-01 dated July 18, 2013, as amended by PCW-DILG-DBM-NEDA JMC No. 2016-01, in planning, implementation, and monitoring of  GAD Fund;
Strengthen the monitoring of fund allocation and expenditures to prevent budget overruns and ensure funds are used as intended;
Conduct regular assessments of the GAD programs and activities to ensure they are realistic, feasible, and align with the objectives of promoting gender equality and empowering women; and
Ensure that the GPB and AR contain reliable data.
